## Tooling 

During the course of that tutorial, we will be using [Angular CLI](https://cli.angular.io/)  to create, build and serve locally the site. If you have not got it installed,  you can do so using NPM:

For that tutorial we are going to use version 1.0.0-RC.1 {.alert .alert-info}

This command will keep the app transpiling and running, watching for any changes in our source code while we continue to build the blog.

Now, we navigate to [http://localhost:4200](http://localhost:4200). 

dr works! {.alert .alert-success}

